@startuml
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center

actor User
participant "Frontend\n(React)" as FE
box "Backend (Spring Boot BFF)" #LightBlue
    participant "Auth Controller" as AC
    participant "Token Exchange\nService" as TES
    participant "Cookie Auth\nFilter" as CAF
    participant "Token Validation\nService" as TVS
    participant "API Controller" as API
end box
database "Redis\n(Token Cache)" as Redis #Pink
database "MSAL_TOKEN_CACHE\n(Encrypted Cookie)" as CookieCache #LightGreen
participant "Entra ID\n(Azure AD)" as Entra

note over Redis, CookieCache
  Two token cache backends — choose one:
  **Option A — Redis** (default): app.token-cache.type=redis
    Clustered deployments; cache lives server-side.
  **Option B — Cookie**: app.token-cache.type=cookie
    Single-instance / no-Redis deployments; cache stored in
    an AES-256-GCM-encrypted HTTP-only cookie (MSAL_TOKEN_CACHE).
    Only RefreshToken + Account sections are persisted.
end note

== Authentication Flow ==

User -> FE : Clicks Login
FE -> AC : GET /api/auth/login
AC -> AC : Generate PKCE Verifier & Challenge
AC -> AC : Generate UUID state (CSRF protection)
note right of AC : State + verifier stored in short-lived\nHttpOnly SameSite=Lax cookies.\nNo server-side session needed.
AC -> TES : generateAuthorizationUrl(scopes, state, challenge)
TES -> AC : Auth URL (PKCE S256 + prompt=select_account)
AC -> User : HTTP 302 Redirect to Entra ID\n(OAUTH_STATE + PKCE_VERIFIER cookies set)

User -> Entra : Authenticate & Consent
Entra -> AC : GET /api/auth/callback?code=...&state=...\n(via Browser Redirect — cookies travel with request)

AC -> AC : Read OAUTH_STATE cookie\nValidate state param (CSRF check — reject on mismatch)
AC -> AC : Read PKCE_VERIFIER cookie\nClear both OAuth flow cookies
AC -> TES : exchangeAuthorizationCode(code, verifier)
TES -> Entra : POST /token\n(code + code_verifier + client_secret + redirect_uri)
Entra -> TES : ID Token + Access Token + Refresh Token
note right of TES : Access & Refresh Tokens stay server-side.\nThey are NEVER sent to the browser in plain text.

alt Option A — Redis cache
    TES -> Redis : afterCacheAccess: write encrypted MSAL cache\n(key: msal:token-cache:{oid.tid}, AES-256-GCM)
    note right of Redis : Per-user isolation by homeAccountId (oid.tid).\nShared across all BFF replicas in the cluster.
else Option B — Cookie cache
    TES -> CookieCache : afterCacheAccess: write MSAL_TOKEN_CACHE cookie\n(AES-256-GCM encrypted, HttpOnly, SameSite=Strict)
    note right of CookieCache : Only RefreshToken + Account sections stored.\nPayload ≈ 300–800 bytes after compress + encrypt.\nBound to this browser — no clustering.
end

TES -> AC : IAuthenticationResult

AC -> AC : Extract ID Token (aud=clientId)
note right of AC : homeAccountId NOT stored in session.\nIt is derived from oid+tid JWT claims\non every request — fully stateless.
AC -> AC : Set HTTP-only Secure cookie: AUTH_TOKEN
AC -> User : HTTP 302 Redirect to Frontend /?login=success

== Authenticated API Request ==

User -> FE : Access Protected Feature
FE -> CAF : GET /api/hello\n(Browser sends AUTH_TOKEN cookie automatically)
CAF -> CAF : Extract ID Token from cookie
CAF -> TVS : validateToken(idToken)
TVS -> TVS : Verify JWK signature (cached from Entra)\nCheck exp, iss (tenantId), aud (clientId)
TVS -> CAF : valid / invalid
CAF -> CAF : Extract username + roles from JWT claims\nSet UsernamePasswordAuthenticationToken in SecurityContext
CAF -> API : Forward authenticated request
API -> FE : JSON Response (e.g., "Hello <name>!")
FE -> User : Display Data

== Silent Token Refresh (AUTH_TOKEN present, expiring within 5 min) ==

note over CAF : Only triggered when AUTH_TOKEN is\npresent and valid but expiring within 5 minutes.\n**Invalid or tampered tokens are not refreshed.**
CAF -> CAF : Parse oid + tid claims from AUTH_TOKEN\nDerive homeAccountId = oid.tid
CAF -> TES : acquireTokenSilently(homeAccountId, scopes)

alt Option A — Redis cache
    TES -> Redis : beforeCacheAccess: read encrypted MSAL cache\n(key: msal:token-cache:{oid.tid})
    note right of Redis : If Redis unavailable: log WARN, empty cache\n(forces full re-exchange, no 500 error).
    Redis -> TES : Cached MSAL token JSON (decrypted)
else Option B — Cookie cache
    TES -> CookieCache : beforeCacheAccess: read MSAL_TOKEN_CACHE cookie\n(decrypt AES-256-GCM, decompress, deserialize)
    note right of CookieCache : Decryption errors (key rotation, tampered)\nare logged and treated as empty cache.
    CookieCache -> TES : Cached MSAL token JSON (RefreshToken + Account)
end

TES -> TES : Look up IAccount from deserialized cache
TES -> Entra : Use cached refresh token\n(POST /token with refresh_token grant)
Entra -> TES : New ID Token + Access Token

alt Option A — Redis cache
    TES -> Redis : afterCacheAccess: write updated cache entry
else Option B — Cookie cache
    TES -> CookieCache : afterCacheAccess: update MSAL_TOKEN_CACHE cookie
end

TES -> CAF : Optional<IAuthenticationResult>
CAF -> CAF : Validate new ID token\nUpdate AUTH_TOKEN cookie\nSet new SecurityContext
note right of CAF : If refresh token expired/revoked,\nOptional is empty → user gets 401\nand must re-authenticate.

== Session Restore (AUTH_TOKEN absent, MSAL cache present) ==

note over CAF : AUTH_TOKEN cookie has expired (MaxAge elapsed)\nbut MSAL_TOKEN_CACHE cookie is still present.\nThis path is primary for **cookie cache mode**;\nRedis mode has no MSAL_TOKEN_CACHE cookie and\ncannot restore sessions without a homeAccountId.
CAF -> CAF : No AUTH_TOKEN → check MSAL_TOKEN_CACHE cookie\n(authCookieService.getMsalCacheCookie)
CAF -> TES : acquireTokenSilentlyFromCache(scopes)

TES -> CookieCache : getAccounts() → beforeCacheAccess:\n  read MSAL_TOKEN_CACHE cookie, deserialize cache
CookieCache -> TES : IAccount (first cached account)
TES -> Entra : Use cached refresh token\n(POST /token with refresh_token grant)
Entra -> TES : New ID Token + Access Token
TES -> CookieCache : afterCacheAccess: update MSAL_TOKEN_CACHE cookie
TES -> CAF : Optional<IAuthenticationResult>
CAF -> CAF : Validate new ID token\nSet AUTH_TOKEN cookie (session re-established)\nSet SecurityContext
note right of CAF : If no cached account or refresh token expired,\nOptional is empty → user gets 401 and must log in again.

== Logout ==

User -> FE : Clicks Logout
FE -> AC : POST /api/auth/logout
AC -> AC : Read AUTH_TOKEN cookie\nParse oid + tid claims\nDerive homeAccountId = oid.tid

alt Option A — Redis cache
    AC -> Redis : Evict cache entry (DELETE msal:token-cache:{oid.tid})
    note right of Redis : Immediate invalidation — prevents\nevicted refresh token being reused\non any pod in the cluster.
else Option B — Cookie cache
    AC -> CookieCache : clearMsalCacheCookie (Max-Age=0)
    note right of CookieCache : Browser deletes MSAL_TOKEN_CACHE immediately.\nNext request with this browser cannot restore session.
end

AC -> AC : Set AUTH_TOKEN cookie with maxAge=0
AC -> FE : 200 OK (browser deletes cookie)
FE -> User : Show unauthenticated state

@enduml
